Anitec Image Technology Corp israising 75 mln dlrs via an issue of convertible subordinateddebentures due 2012 with a 5-7/8 pct coupon and par pricing,said lead manager Smith Barney, Harris Upham and Co Inc.    The debentures are convertible into the company's commonstock at 32 dlrs a share, representing a 26.73 pct premium overthe stock price when terms on the debt were set.    Non-callable for two years, the debentures are rated B-2 byMoody's and B by Standard and Poor's. Donaldson Lufkin, SalomonBrothers and Mabon Nugent co-managed the issue, which wasincreased from an initial offering of 60 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;